```

### `src/types.ts` — interfaces retained verbatim, comments updated

The three `VisionDoc`/`ChargeDoc`/`PieceDoc` interfaces become projection shapes (not BookEntry rows). Per the brief the definitions are retained verbatim. The `[key: string]: unknown` index signature is harmless to keep.

Post-cleanup, `VisionDoc.createdAt` and `VisionDoc.updatedAt` project from `writ.createdAt`/`writ.updatedAt` rather than being written to a companion book. The field names and types are identical; only the data source changes.

**concurrent doc updates needed:** top-of-file comment says "shadows each one with a typed companion document stored in its own book" — update to describe projection shapes.

### `src/tools/render.ts` — comment updates only; function contracts unchanged

`composeShow<TDoc>(doc, id, clerk)`: receives the typed-API result (now a projection) and fetches the writ separately via `clerk.show(id)`. Still correct post-cleanup — the "doc" is the projection, the "writ" is the underlying WritDoc.

